0;s:75:"After the garage door is closed firmly press the garage door opener button.";i:41;s:105:"Once you are done with the initial check-up make sure to remove any source of power from the garage door.";i:42;s:78:"Unplug the opener and remove any battery that is connected to the garage door.";i:43;s:40:"Look for the Red Emergency Release Cord.";i:44;s:206:"If you ever find yourself in that dreaded situation where the power is out but you need your garage door to open follow these steps to safely opening your garage door without the help of the trolley system.";i:45;s:36:"Opening a Garage Door Without Power.";i:46;s:95:"More often than not when the power goes out your garage door is already in the closed position.";i:47;s:70:"If your garage door springs are failing the door will feel very heavy.";i:48;s:95:"This would be a nice time to consult a professional to discuss options for fixing your springs.";i:49;s:28:"Secure the Garage Door Rope.";i:50;s:167:"If you are experiencing an extended outage or will need to manually open and close the door many times secure the rope back and away from the tracks the door rides on.";i:51;s:97:"If the rope becomes stuck in the door as it slides up you will have another problem to deal with.";i:52;s:20:"Put the Garage Door.";i:53;s:96:"Once your car is out of the garage close the door and reconnect the trolley to the Tshaped stem.";i:54;s:171:"To ensure that everything has been done properly you will hear a click sound and will notice that the door is well engaged with the engine trolley while trying to lift it.";i:55;s:38:"Make Sure the Garage Door Isnt Locked.";i:56;s:92:"If you secure your garage door with a manual lock check to see if its in place at this time.";i:57;s:70:"If so remove the lock so you can open the door without causing damage.";i:58;s:30:"Open the Garage Door Manually.";i:59;s:68:"There should be a handle somewhere on the inside of the garage door.";i:60;s:24:"Grab it and lift upward.";i:61;s:75:"Pull the emergency cord to disconnect the door from the garage door opener.";i:62;s:103:"The cord usually has a red handle and will hang down from the center rail of the garage door mechanism.";i:63;s:62:"Lift the garage door straight up until the door is fully open.";i:64;s:71:"Make sure the door will remain fully open before leaving it unattended.";i:65;s:83:"This will cause the trolley to move into position and reconnect to the garage door.";i:66;s:175:"3 locate the lifting handle to open the door and lift it up without forcing use the lifting handle very often installed in the bottom panel or sometimes in the second section.";i:67;s:31:"Ad excellence is our guarantee.";i:68;s:73:"With your key unlock the door and turn the handle so that it is vertical.";i:69;s:119:"Pull the garage door straight up with your hands and make sure it stays open before driving your car inside the garage.";i:70;s:65:"When youre inside pull the garage door down to a closed position.";}}